Jose Mourinho has rewarded his players with two days off before they start preparations for Wednesday’s Champions League clash with Paris Saint-Germain.

Chelsea have come through a critical period in the fixture list with victory in the Capital One Cup final against Tottenham at Wembley last Sunday and last night’s 1-0 win at West Ham.

Mourinho’s players will return to training at the weekend as the Chelsea manager plots the second leg against Laurent Blanc’s side at Stamford Bridge.

